description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Berkshire Specialist Wheelchair Service is looking for an enthusiastic Occupational Therapist or Physiotherapist with an interest in working with people with complex health and postural needs. The post is for 37.5 hours, 5 days per week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You could be part of our friendly team at East Berkshire Specialist Wheelchair Service. Based in beautiful Royal Berkshire we cover the East of&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Berkshire and provide wheelchairs and specialist seating to a broad range of people (adults and children) including those with complex&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are now based in a newly renovated location at 3, Abell Gardens in Maidenhead providing staff and patients with hugely improved environment and facilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working alongside a high performing team of specialist Physiotherapist, Occupational Therapists, Rehab Engineer and Technicians and administration team, which is finalist at HSJ Patient Safety Awards 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate should have a broad range of clinical experience in variety of in-patient and outpatient settings and should have experience of working with physically disabled patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant must have a valid driving licence and their own car as they will be asked to travel within Berkshire and some parts of Buckinghamshire as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The applicant must be flexible, a good team member and have good communication skills. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All applicants must be on the HCPC register and will undergo enhanced DBS clearance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be appointed to Band 6 and the s&lt;strong&gt;alary will range from £32,933 to £39,681 &lt;/strong&gt;per annum &lt;strong&gt;pro rata (incl of HCAS) &lt;/strong&gt;depending on experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information or to organize a visit to service please call 01628 670117 and speak to Kashmira Sangle, Clinical Lead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
